	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories KwaZulu-Natal police are investigating an inquest docket after the roof of a house that was being renovated collapsed on a 37-year-old mother and her one-year-old daughter, killing them both, police said on Friday. The incident happened in Shallcross, near Chatsworth in Durban on Friday morning, according to police. ALSO READ: Toddler found lying over baby sister after both die in Cape Town blaze KZN police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbhele told News24 that, according to information she has received, the house where the two died was undergoing renovation. Mbhele said she had been told that three other people were injured and rushed to hospital. "We can confirm that an inquest docket was opened at Chatsworth police station for investigation," she said. ALSO READ: Four-month-old baby found alive at 'horror' crime scene KZN Emergency Medical Services spokesperson Robert McKenzie said their paramedics were part of the emergency teams that responded to the incident. "We found that a woman aged 37-years-old and her one-year-old daughter had sustained fatal injuries during the roof collapse," said McKenzie.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  